## Additional Notes / Comments
`train_model.py` and `app.py` are intentionally decoupled: retraining the model (e.g., after adding
more data) only requires re-running `train_model.py` to refresh `model.pkl` — no changes to the
Flask app are needed as long as the feature order stays the same.
